originalText.text: I needed a last minute appointment for a dislodged filling. I was able to easily make an appointment online. When I arrived to Tend Chelsea the check in process was seamless. I saw the dentist shortly after X-rays were taken, given a quote on the out of pocket expenses and had my filling replaced all under 45 minutes. This is not what my typical experience is at previous dentist visits. I am highly impressed and will be switching my dental care to Tend permanently (or as long as I‚Äôm in NYC)! Thank you Tend for the amazing experience.

originalText.text:
This place is a joke. I did my breezy braces here and the experience was ok at best. But thats not why I am leaving a one star review.

It's the post care that has me fuming. I needed a set of retainers so I send a bunch of emails just looking to order a set of replacement ones. Nothing more, nothing less.

They pass me off to a bunch of folks on this email thread. I get frustrated so I go in person and ask to speak to someone. They make me come in for a scan which I didn't see the point. Whatever, I need these retainers.

Then they do a scan and they quote me $600 for a replacement. What in hell is this? Ive gotten retainers from a local mom and pop shop and NEVER paid more than $200. I couldn't help but feel like this was a shakedown.

Don't get braces here. Get them from a local mom and post shop. The post care is awful. In hindsight I would have gotten my ortho from another place although the Doc doing the ortho at this location was really great.

I rarely write one star reviews. I won't be coming to tend anymore. And i regret giving them my business.
